<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="great-adj">great <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɡreɪt/    美 /ɡreɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>大的；巨大的；重大的；伟大的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the great mountains 
崇山峻岭</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a great discovery
伟大的发现</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(数量 / 程度等) 极大的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The <strong>great majority of</strong> people seem to agree with this view. 
大多数人似乎都同意这种观点。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The more fat you take in before bedtime, the greater burden you will put on your body at night.
睡前摄入的脂肪越多，夜间你的身体承受的负担就越重。</p><footer>2016 四川</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That was a great while ago.
那是很久以前的事了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-wonderful">3.★ <strong>美妙的；极好的 (wonderful)；崇高的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I've got the use of a car.
我弄到了一辆小汽车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— That's great!
好极了！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>great thoughts
崇高的思想</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— We can give you a ride into town.
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ Thank you.  （2011 陕西）<br />
A.Yes, why not?<br />
B.Oh, it would be my pleasure.<br />
C.Yes, please.<br />
D.Oh, that would be great.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  </p></div>